                  <summary>Papyrus letter from the Arsinoites (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt. Letter is from Diophantos to Apollonios, a collector of taxes from those away from their own towns</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 11.2 x 16.4 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">8 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto; written along the fibers on the verso, inverse to the text on the recto. The word "Apollonioi" appears in large letters</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 2.5 cm.; lower margin of 2.5 cm.; left margin of 2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage with P.Duk.inv. 678-681 and 683-690</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 682 was formerly P.Duk.inv. MF79 9</note>
